=== Sprint 2 · Task S2.2: SearchBroker → real mtapi Search RPC ===
Date: 2026-05-27
Plan: docs/plan/2026-05-27-整改与执行计划.md §4.S2.2

--- Problem ---
V2 §2.D-3 / plan S2.2: AccountServer.SearchBroker returned a single hardcoded broker
(Exness) regardless of user input. The mtapi gRPC Service.Search RPC existed in both
mt4 and mt5 proto stubs but was never called.

--- Fix ---
Part 1 — internal/mdgateway/adapter/brokersearch/search.go (NEW):
- Searcher struct: mt4Gateway + mt5Gateway (defaults to mtapi prod gateways)
- Search(ctx, company, mtType): routes to mt4, mt5, or both
- searchMT4 / searchMT5: gRPC Dial → NewServiceClient → Search RPC → disconnect
- mapMT4Reply / mapMT5Reply: pure functions mapping mtapi Company/Result to ant BrokerCompany/BrokerServer

Part 2 — internal/connect/user/account_handler.go (MODIFIED):
- Added searcher *brokersearch.Searcher field + SetSearcher() setter
- SearchBroker: calls searcher.Search() if available → returns real results
- Falls back to static Exness entry when searcher is nil or call fails

Part 3 — cmd/server/main.go (MODIFIED):
- Added import for brokersearch package
- brokersearch.New("", "") injected into accountServer via SetSearcher()

